{{DISPLAYTITLE: '''<span style="font-family: Casino; color: #FFEA00; text-shadow: 0 0 12px #FFEA00, 0 0 22px #FFD700, 0 0 32px #D4A017;"> Level 776: Jackpot! </span>'''}}

Level 776 is the lucky '''''777'''''<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms.

{{Class Custom Image|text-color=red|extra-banner-css=|bg-image=Slots.gif|color-h=31|safety=Safe|security=Secure|entity=Friendly Entities|class=0|hexagon=0}}

==<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>Description</span>==

Level 776 is an infinite casino where one can gamble. The casino itself has all the traditional games one would find in a frontroom casino. They will accept whatever currency one may have for ships; or they may trade in what other items one may have for chips. The chip runner will deem what the item is worth if an item is handed to them. The chip runner will again ask if they are sure they want to trade in the item, up to the wanderer if they truly want to hand it in or not. 
{{Blurimage|file=Casino Floor.png||caption=Photo of an empty floor taken at the Casino.}}
If one accepts, they will be handed the casino chips. The chips themselves will come in different colors and in different values up to a maximum of 25k US dollars or whatever equates to a currency is used in any group one may come from. The currency any wanderers hand to the chip runners will equate to the chips they will get. Any items the wanderer's trade in for chips, the chips will automatically equate to the rate of the US dollar. Although if one requests a different form of currency to trade the chips in for instead of the original currency they used prior to getting the casino chips, they may do so. They also may trade in chips in exchange for whatever item was traded in.

Once one gets the chips, they may use them at any tables or slots one may find throughout the casino. Any wanderer trying to cheat will be instantly caught by cameras watching them and will be ejected from the casino and will be permanently barred from entering the level again. Same case for anyone stealing casino chips.

===<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>Prizes</span>===

There are prizes one may get for winning games. If one manages to achieve 500 dollars' worth of winnings, they will be awarded 5 free meals at whatever restaurant they may head to. If one manages to achieve 25k dollars' worth of winnings, they will be given a ticket for a free casino themed assault rifle. When one plans to leave the casino and cash in their chips, they can also give the ticket to the chip runner, and they will receive the rifle although it will be empty. When one leaves the level however, it will be loaded with a full magazine. In addition, five more magazine rounds will appear in a separate given backpack to them.

When one manages to achieve 50k dollars' worth of winnings, they will be awarded free food from all the restaurants in the casino for one year. In addition, they will receive a ticket for full-body tactical armor that is casino themed. Just like the rifle, one can redeem the ticket to the chip runner, and they will get the full-body tactical armor. 

Whenever one manages to get 100k dollars' worth of winnings, they will be awarded a specially made drink. This drink is reported to be an inspiration of the red type of Almond Water, and like it will enhance blood circulation and wound healing. There are other properties however that make it special. It will also cure any sickness any wanderer has and will increase their strength three times the normal human limit. The drink has a cherry flavor taste and lasts for 48 hours.

If one manages to get 250k dollars' worth of winnings, they will receive three of these drinks and will also be granted permission from Mr. Carratelli himself that they will be granted free food and drinks for all time in any of the casino restaurants. If one manages to acquire 500k dollars' worth of winnings, they will be granted ten of the enhanced cherry drinks. 

If one manages to reach the grand goal of one million dollars' worth of winnings, Mr. Carratelli will personally congratulate them and throw a big celebration for them in the casino that lasts for three hours. After three hours of celebration, they will receive a special prize. They will be led to the '''''Blessed Exit'''''.


===<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>The Restaurants</span>===
{{Blurimage|file=Casino Restaurant.png||caption=A photo of a restaurant themed to the Southern United States.}}
The Restaurants in the casino are areas designed for the wanderer to take breaks in and to settle any thirsts or hunger one may have while in the casino. The Restaurants themselves will all have different themes each, mainly casino themes. Although there will international themes with some themed to regions of any specific country that have existed through history, though they must be well-known.

The food offered in these restaurants will be casino themed regardless of the theme of the restaurant. Although if one does eat at a restaurant specifically themed to a certain region or country, they will have exclusive dishes at that restaurant found nowhere else in the casino.

==<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>Entities And The Human</span>==

===<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>Facelings</span>===

Facelings are the entities that reside in the casino. They take on the role of employees at the casino under the eye of Mr. Carratelli ranging from chip runners, waiters, and other functions the casino needs to operate. They routinely go on breaks and drink and eat at the restaurants. They will also engineer and build the casino-themed rifles and full-body tactical armors that they hand out as prizes.

===<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>Mr. Carratelli</span>===
{{Blurimage|file=Mr. Carratelli.jpg||caption=Body portrait of Mr. Carratelli.}}
Mr. Carratelli is the chairman of the casino and the one who oversees everything in the level. He is described as wearing a black and white suit, wearing a fedora, and always smoking no matter where he is. He may only appear to people who have won 250k or more in winnings as he's described himself "only wanting to hang out with the big winners".  He is described as a friendly individual, with the few people meeting him describing him as a kind man who always gives free cigarette to the big winners. 

It is largely unknown where he came from how he became the chairman of the casino. There are however some pieces of evidence that he was formerly part of the [[M.E.G.]] indicating that at one point he was a high-ranking member there. It is however unknown when he joined and left the organization, but it is rumored he left to pursue take the role of chairman.

==<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>Groups and Organizations</span>==

===<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>The Gamblers Group</span>===

The Gamblers Group is a group of around 43 individuals all united in their goals to get to a million dollars each in order to reach the blessed exit. Together they try and form strategies around all the games in the casino in order to further their chances of winning the prizes necessary. They often invite people to join their group and offer them a free suit for joining and will teach them everything they know in order to win big. In exchange for joining them, they must stay in the level for one year and must distribute their earnings to all members of the group.

==<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>Entrances and Exits</span>==

==<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>Entrances</span>==

If one manages to find a casino chip in the grainy fields of [[Level 232]] and walk one mile, they will find an abandoned looking casino. Enter it, and they will be brought here.

If one manages to find an entrance to a casino in [[Level 320]] and enter it, they will be brought here.

If one manages to find a black fedora on [[Level 153]] or [[Level 906.1]] and wear it and sit in a chair, they will fall asleep and wake up in the casino.

If one sees a mysterious figure wearing a mysterious suit and fedora within [[Level 416]] and chases them, after some time they will find a hole, and the trees around them will have card symbols. (Hearts, Diamonds, Spades and Clubs.) Jump into the hole, and they will be brought here.

==<span style="font-family:Casino; color: #ff1212;>Exits</span>==

If one manages to win a million chips, they will be led to the '''''Blessed Exit'''''. Mr. Carratelli alone will guide them alone to a secret door only known to him and no one else and with a password only known to him. He will put earmuffs on the wanderer so as not to reveal the password. Once he speaks the password, the door will open and Mr. Carratelli will remove the earmuffs. Once one then enters the door, they will be led to [[Level 399]].

When one turns in their chips and gets whatever currency they are paid in and get their prizes if they have any, they will be led to glass double doors, which will lead them to a random Class 0 or Class 1 level.

